body.body: Replacement Chassis ECM Setup - Tech Bulletin Introduction
Replacement chassis ECMs can be setup on the above models using the Triumph diagnostic tool.
The instruction below details the steps necessary to complete the setup process. This instruction replaces the process detailed in the Service Manual.
Note - Battery Voltage Check and Charger Use
Before starting the setup procedure, make sure the battery voltage is at least 12.8 Volts.
An approved battery charger suitable for use with maintenance free batteries, may be used to maintain battery charge during the setup process.
Replacement Chassis ECM Setup - Preliminary Steps - Key Ignition

Download and install the latest version of the Triumph diagnostic tool to your computer as described in the Triumph Diagnostic Tool Installation Guide. Diagnostic tool version 2019-01 or later is required to complete this process.
Switch the engine stop switch to the STOP position.
Replacement Chassis ECM Setup - Partial Update - Key Ignition

A partial chassis ECM update is required to install the software necessary to allow the first key to be paired. It is not possible to complete the full chassis ECM download until after the first key has been paired.
Navigate to DOWNLOAD - CHASSIS ECM DOWNLOAD.
Use manual model selection to select the correct chassis ECM calibration for your model and region.
Place a key in the ignition switch and turn the ignition ON.

Replacement chassis ECMs are delivered with the immobiliser function configured for keyless ignition. It is normal for the download process to behave in the same way as a keyless ignition model at this stage.
At the start of the download, Do NOT turn the ignition OFF when prompted to do so by the diagnostic tool. Click Next and the download will start as normal.
The chassis ECM immobiliser configuration is changed to key ignition during the first key pairing process.
When prompted by the diagnostic tool to turn the ignition OFF, keep the ignition turned ON and click
Allow the download progress to reach 100%.

Replacement Chassis ECM Setup - Pair First Key - Key Ignition
Navigate to CHASSIS DIAGNOSTICS - IMMOBILISER DIAGNOSTICS - Configure.
Replacement chassis ECMs are supplied with the immobiliser function configured for keyless ignition by default.

When adding the first key to Tiger 1200 XR models, make sure Key Ignition is selected when you are prompted to select an immobiliser type. A 600 second time delay is started when Key Ignition is selected.

If Keyless ignition is selected by mistake, a 300 second time delay will be started. In this situation, If a key is allowed to pair, It will not be possible to change the immobiliser type again using the diagnostic tool. Click Cancel before the countdown reaches zero seconds and restart the pairing process.
When prompted to select an immobiliser type, click
Wait for the 600 second time delay to complete.
When the key has paired, click
Turn the ignition OFF. Wait 30 seconds to allow the chassis ECM to power down.
Replacement Chassis ECM Setup - Full Update
It is now possible to download the full chassis ECM calibration.
Navigate to DOWNLOAD - CHASSIS ECM DOWNLOAD.
Use automatic model selection to select the correct chassis ECM calibration for your model and region.
Follow all on screen instructions and allow the download to complete as normal.
Replacement Chassis/Keyless ECM Setup - Pair the Engine ECM
Switch the engine stop switch to the RUN position.
Navigate to CHASSIS DIAGNOSTICS - IMMOBILISER DIAGNOSTICS - Configure.
Wait for the 300 second time delay to complete.
Replacement Chassis ECM Setup - Pair Second Key - Models with Maximum 2 Keys
Place the second key in the ignition switch and turn the ignition ON.
function to pair the second key.
Wait for the time delay to complete.
Replacement Chassis/Keyless ECM Setup - Final Steps
Check all ECMs for stored DTCs and erase as necessary.
Make sure that the engine can be started using each key. After each key is tested, turn the ignition OFF and allow one minute for the motorcycle to fully power down before testing the next key.
If fitted, set up the Tyre Pressure Monitoring System as described in the Triumph Diagnostic Tool User Guide.
Please mark your copy of the Service Manual with this information.
